The term populism came into use The term populism came into use to describe a political movement that promises to give voice to the concerns of ordinary people.
In 1967 a Conference on Populism In 1967, a Conference on Populism convened to explore the rise of grassroot movements challenging the Establishment, seeking to empower the common citizen against what they perceived as an elitist governance. The gathering was both a diagnosis of a perceived democratic malaise and a call to action for political reformers around the world.
